<subSubSection id="9D9E8287BB7FE7688E221D6A985EA714" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="8D603CEECBA8B321B5058A4B35DC4CDD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D11F29CB941E741BBE4552C6B8D5F09" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Two specimens belonging to the original material are housed at LY: LY0682162 and LY0088790. Both are in good condition. We have designated here the most complete one as the lectotype.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5767C659602130788B33E14CBA907904" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This specimen conforms to the description of the protologue and corresponds to the current application of the name, which is considered a distinct species by 
<bibRefCitation id="F6D5871D219417D4B321D7D83A5094B1" author="Tison, J-M" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B37" refString="Tison, J-M, de Foucault, B, 2014. Flora Gallica. Flore de France. Biotope Editons, Meze." title="Flora Gallica. Flore de France. Biotope Editons, Meze." year="2014">Tison and de Foucault (2014)</bibRefCitation>
. The lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="151B481F3EF9CA34F7344603E0C079EB" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. saxicola" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="saxicola">
<emphasis id="BC2C730C3B0124CD597CBEED573D2F21" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. saxicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 10-15 cm long basal leaves and multiflorous scapes; concerning the shape of calyx teeth, it is very similar to the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="F773EB52074A5854E1F0784A6FF954C0" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. inodorus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="inodorus">
<emphasis id="65EDAEB0F934F296370A60F73BC509B3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. inodorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Gaertn., which in turn is currently included within the variability of 
<taxonomicName id="E7D07B3FB7CF3EB6A149F354FC778714" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. sylvestris" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="sylvestris">
<emphasis id="17B2BBA77DFDE2B1829F29E034652803" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. sylvestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="7D7A1598E535B6E772D561C47B0F37C3" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12563" author="Domina, G" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1096 - 1100" refId="B15" refString="Domina, G, Astuti, G, Barone, G, Gargano, D, Minuto, L, Varaldo, L, Peruzzi, L, 2021. Lectotypification of the name Dianthus virgineus and consequences within the D. sylvestris group (Caryophyllaceae). Taxon 70 (5): 1096 - 1100, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12563" title="Lectotypification of the name Dianthus virgineus and consequences within the D. sylvestris group (Caryophyllaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12563" volume="70" year="2021">Domina et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
). Further research is needed to clarify the relationships between these two taxa.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
